From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Igor Velkov <iav@iav.lv>
Date: Tue, 22 Jul 2026 05:30:00 +0000
Subject: arm64: dts: rockchip: cap SPI NOR frequency on ROCK Pi 4A

Commit fa16d7a820e4 ("arm64: dts: rockchip: Increase maximum frequency of
SPI flash for ROCK Pi 4A/B/C") raised spi-max-frequency from 10 MHz to the
108 MHz the XT25F32 datasheet allows. On this ROCK Pi 4A that rate is not
usable.

The Rockchip SPI controller is clocked from GPLL/16 = 37.125 MHz and divides
by an even factor: 108 MHz (clamped by the driver to 50 MHz) selects /2 =
18.56 MHz. At that SCLK the XT25F32 on this board returns corrupt data on
bulk transfers - the JEDEC id read still succeeds (so an mtd device appears),
but flashcp fails verification at an offset that moves between runs, which
makes writing a bootloader to SPI unreliable. /4 = 9.28 MHz is stable.

Restore the pre-fa16d7a value of 10 MHz, which selects the /4 divider and was
the working default for years. With it, flashcp writes and verifies the
u-boot SPI image cleanly and the board boots from SPI.

Only ROCK Pi 4A is changed here: 4B and 4C carry the same value but were not
tested, and the original change was reported as tested on a 4A, so board
revisions may differ.

Signed-off-by: Igor Velkov <iav@iav.lv>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3399-rock-pi-4a.dts | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3399-rock-pi-4a.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3399-rock-pi-4a.dts
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3399-rock-pi-4a.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3399-rock-pi-4a.dts
@@ -19,6 +19,6 @@
 	flash@0 {
 		compatible = "jedec,spi-nor";
 		reg = <0>;
-		spi-max-frequency = <108000000>;
+		spi-max-frequency = <10000000>;
 	};
 };
